  "whats_new": "Bounced ~3% back above $64,000 as risk appetite returned with the VIX crashing \u2014 but it's still below both its 50-day (~$65,700) and 200-day (~$74,200) averages, so this is a bounce inside a downtrend, not a trend change. Needs a close above ~$65,700 to signal a real turn; first support ~$63,300.",
